===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|might|lang=enm}}, {{term|myghte|lang=enm}}, (also {{term|maught|lang=enm}}, {{term|macht|lang=enm}}, {{term|maht|lang=enm}}), from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|miht|lang=ang}}, {{term|mieht|lang=ang}}, {{term|meaht|lang=ang}}, {{term|mæht||might, bodily strength, power, authority, ability, virtue, mighty work, miracle, angel|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|mahtiz|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|mahtuz||might, power|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|mógʰtis|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|magʰ-||to allow, be able, help|lang=ine-pro}}, corresponding to Germanic {{term|maganan|maganą|lang=gem-pro}} + {{term|-þiz|lang=gem-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|micht|lang=sco}}, {{term|maucht||might|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|macht||might, ability|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|macht||might, ability|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|macht||might, power|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Macht||power, might|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|makt||might|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|máttur||might|lang=is}}.

